sentences: Nobu Kōda 幸田延 (1870–1946) was a Japanese composer, violinist, and music teacher.
Nobu Kōda was born on April 19, 1870.
She graduated from the Institute in 1885 as part of the first graduating class.
She went to Boston and studied at the New England Conservatory in 1889 at the age of 19.
She studied in Vienna through 1895 before returning once again to Japan.
In 1892 she went to Germany and studied there with Joseph Joachim.
Nobu Kōda would leave for Europe again in 1909, though would once again return to Japan, where she lived until her death in 1946.
